newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia rubber ends mixed on weak interest.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia rubber ends mixed on weak interest.

text.p: Malaysian rubber prices ended mixed due to little interest from overseas consumer markets already showing signs of year-end holiday lethargy, traders said.
"I guess it's going to be like this the whole month," said a trader with a sigh after failing to note any business for the first trading day of December.
Dealers said apart from uncertainties usually associated with the start of a new week, Monday's trading was notably gloomier with the virtual absence of U.S. and European dealers.
"The U.S. dealers are still not through the lethargy of the long Thanksgiving weekend," said a Kuala Lumpur-based trader.
At the close, the Malaysian Rubber Exchange and Licensing Board quoted December RSS1 buyer at 317 cents ($) a kg, down half cent from Friday's close. December SMR 20 was a cent higher at 306.50.
Traders offered the SMR CV at 366 cents, SMR L at 346, SMR 5 at 322, SMR 10 at 314, SMR 20 at 311 and drum latex at 237.
The INRO five-day moving average fell to 241.95 Malaysian/Singapore cents per kg on Nov 29 from 242.14 on Nov 28. The daily indicator price dipped to 242.71 from 243.05.
